  "assemblySteps": [
    "Make petal units using stitch-and-flip method: draw diagonal on wrong side of 2-inch Fabric 25 squares, position on corner of 3.5-inch Red square, stitch on line, trim, press. Add 2-inch Fabric 17 square to opposite corner. Make 2 Petal 1 and 2 Petal 2 units per block.",
    "Make leaf units: draw diagonal on wrong side of 3.5-inch and 2-inch Fabric 25 squares. Position 3.5-inch square on bottom of 3.5 x 5 inch green rectangle, stitch, trim, press. Add 2-inch square to opposite top corner. Make 1 Leaf 1 and 1 Leaf 2 per block using same green fabric.",
    "Arrange and sew 4 Petal units and 2 Leaf units together to make a Rose Block. Make 32 Rose Blocks.",
    "For Trellis Blocks: stitch Fabric 25 strips to sides of each Light rectangle, then to top and bottom. Make 31 Trellis Blocks.",
    "Arrange blocks alternately on a large flat surface, making sure no fabric is close to itself. Join into 7 rows of 9 blocks each. Join the rows.",
    "Sew long borders to the sides. Sew short borders to the top and bottom.",
    "Layer the quilt with batting and backing and baste. Quilt in the ditch around borders and patches. Bind to finish the quilt."
  ],
